@startuml turn_signal_to_body_gateway_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Turn Signal To Body Gateway Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> Router -> BCM -> CoreState / CLU)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Turn Cmd" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "INPUT_CONSOLE_ROUTER\nturn command normalizer" as Router #FFF4CC
participant "BCM\nbody lamp owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "CoreState\nturn lamp mirror" as CoreState #FCE8FF
participant "CLU\nlamp readback consumer" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Turn Command Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Click OFF / LEFT / RIGHT / HAZ
activate Panel
Panel -> Router : Cmd::turnOff / turnLeft /\nturnRight / turnHazard
note right of Panel
Panel emits one-shot button pulses.
end note
deactivate Panel

== Router Normalization ==

activate Router
Router -> Router : map pulses to Cmd::turnSignalCmd
Router -> Router : OFF=0 LEFT=1 RIGHT=2 HAZARD=3
Router -> BCM : Cmd::turnSignalCmd
note right of Router
Representative seams
- Cmd::turnSignalCmd
- Cmd::turnHazard
end note
deactivate Router

== BCM Lamp Ownership ==

activate BCM
BCM -> BCM : manualMode = (Test::scenarioActiveId == 0)
BCM -> BCM : hazardActive from effective alert level >= 6
BCM -> BCM : if manualMode -> turnLampState = Cmd::turnSignalCmd
BCM -> BCM : else if ETH turn-lamp input fresh -> use gTurnLampInputState
BCM -> BCM : publish frmLampControlMsg /\nfrmHazardControlMsg /\nfrmBodyGatewayStateMsg
BCM -> CoreState : turnLampState
note right of BCM
BCM is the effective body gateway
owner for turn-lamp state.
end note
deactivate BCM

== Downstream Visibility ==

activate CLU
BCM -> CLU : CoreState::turnLampState\nand body lamp frames
CLU -> Panel : FRM / turn readback
deactivate CLU

note over Driver, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console emits turn-command pulses
2. Router normalizes to Cmd::turnSignalCmd
3. BCM owns final turnLampState and hazard publication
4. CoreState / CLU expose the visible lamp readback
end note

@enduml
